President Uhuru Kenyatta and former prime minister Raila Odinga will in the next one and a half months know the fate of their building bridges initiative constitutional amendment drive, in a court ruling seen as critical to next year&rsquo;s presidential polls. But what are the likely political scenarios, and why is the BBI so central to the Kenyatta succession race, and what alternative cards might key presidential hopefuls be hiding ahead of next year&rsquo;s polls? Our senior political affairs reporter Murimi Mwangi examines in this week&rsquo;s house of cards.